### ==========================================
### Notifier Service — HTTP API Examples
### ==========================================
### Usage:
###   1. Install VS Code REST Client extension
###   2. Set variables below (or in VS Code settings)
###   3. Click "Send Request" above each request
### ==========================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:9002
@userToken = YOUR_USER_JWT_TOKEN
@adminToken = YOUR_ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN
@serviceToken = YOUR_SERVICE_JWT_TOKEN
@tenantId = default

### ==========================================
### 1. Health & Readiness
### ==========================================

### Public health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/health/
Accept: application/json

### Public readiness
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/ready
Accept: application/json

### ==========================================
### 2. Service → Notification Creation
### ==========================================

### Create notification (service auth)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service/notifications
Authorization: Bearer {{serviceToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: {{$guid}}
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenantId}}

{
  "userId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
  "type": "in_app",
  "priority": "normal",
  "body": "Hello from service!",
  "subject": "Test Notification"
}

### Create batch notifications
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service/notifications/batch
Authorization: Bearer {{serviceToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notifications": [
    {
      "userId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
      "type": "in_app",
      "body": "Batch item 1"
    },
    {
      "userId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
      "type": "email",
      "body": "Batch item 2",
      "recipientEmail": "test@example.com",
      "subject": "Batch Test"
    }
  ]
}

### ==========================================
### 3. User /me Endpoints
### ==========================================

### List my notifications
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/notifications?page=1&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### Get unread count
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/notifications/unread-count
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### Mark all as read
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/notifications/read-all
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### Get my preferences
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/preferences
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### Update preferences
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/preferences
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "sms",
  "isEnabled": true,
  "allowInstant": true,
  "allowDigest": false
}

### List my reminders
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/reminders
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### ==========================================
### 4. Admin Endpoints
### ==========================================

### Dashboard overview
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/dashboard/overview
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### List all notifications (filter by status=failed)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/notifications?status=failed&page=1&pageSize=20
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Retry a failed notification
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/notifications/NOTIFICATION_ID/retry
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### List delivery attempts for a notification
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/notifications/NOTIFICATION_ID/attempts
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### List providers
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/providers
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Provider health
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/providers/health
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Test provider (dry-run)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/providers/sms-default/test
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "channel": "sms",
  "recipient": "+989121234567",
  "body": "Test notification from admin",
  "dryRun": true
}

### List deliveries
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/deliveries?status=failed&page=1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Retry a delivery
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/deliveries/DELIVERY_ID/retry
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Observability — health (detailed)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/observability/health
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Observability — metrics
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/observability/metrics
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Observability — queue
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/observability/queue
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Observability — workers
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/observability/workers
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### ==========================================
### 5. Templates (Admin)
### ==========================================

### Create template
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/templates
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "welcome-email",
  "type": "email",
  "subject": "Welcome {{userName}}!",
  "body": "Hello {{userName}}, welcome to our service!",
  "variables": ["userName"],
  "isActive": true
}

### Render preview
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/templates/render-preview
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "templateKey": "welcome-email",
  "variables": {
    "userName": "John"
  }
}

### ==========================================
### 6. Reminders
### ==========================================

### Create reminder
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me/reminders
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
  "type": "email",
  "recipient": "user@example.com",
  "subject": "Meeting Reminder",
  "body": "Don't forget the meeting tomorrow!",
  "scheduledAt": "2026-12-01T09:00:00Z"
}

### ==========================================
### 7. Error Scenarios
### ==========================================

### Access admin without token (expect 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/dashboard/overview

### Access admin with user token (expect 403)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/dashboard/overview
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### Retry already-sent notification (expect 409)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/notifications/SENT_NOTIFICATION_ID/retry
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Get non-existent notification (expect 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/notifications/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
